The furnace of judgment is not yours to put people in.

23:07.298 --> 23:16.108
The furnace of judgment is not your place to have a Facebook conversation about what everybody else thinks and why they're so stupid to think it.

23:16.749 --> 23:18.951
I should be preaching like this my first Sunday back in the year.

23:19.311 --> 23:21.714
I might run y'all all off from the church.

23:21.734 --> 23:32.466
But notice in the parable it says that it was his field, and I am learning more and more in my life that if it's his field, that means it's his furnace.

23:33.250 --> 23:37.421
That means God has to be the one to decide who's right and who's wrong.

23:38.002 --> 23:42.454
God has to be the one to decide who is on his side and who is not.

23:42.975 --> 23:50.354
I remember very early in my ministry, there was a pastor that I greatly admired, and he was mentoring me in many ways.

23:50.498 --> 23:55.506
He was bringing up examples of the right kind of ministry and the wrong kind of ministry.

23:56.026 --> 23:59.752
He brought up one minister, and he said, now this guy, he's arrogant.

24:00.113 --> 24:03.438
This guy, he is not doctrinally sound.

24:03.818 --> 24:06.302
This guy, he is not theologically correct.

24:06.562 --> 24:10.288
In fact, you can watch him preach and you can see his pride.

24:10.648 --> 24:14.354
He's arrogant, and he's self-focused, and he's fleshly.

24:14.434 --> 24:18.218
And then he brought up another gentleman and he said, now this man is humble.

24:18.598 --> 24:22.802
This man has the Greek New Testament practically memorized.

24:22.822 --> 24:24.343
He's a serious student.

24:24.363 --> 24:26.385
This man, you can tell by watching him.

24:26.626 --> 24:27.326
He is meek.

24:27.647 --> 24:28.487
He is mild.

24:28.728 --> 24:29.689
He is Christ-like.

24:30.049 --> 24:31.550
That's who you want to be like.

24:31.570 --> 24:34.293
Not this guy over here, that guy right there.

24:34.733 --> 24:43.762
Five years later, the guy who knew Greek, the guy who was so humble was discovered to have been having an affair

24:44.162 --> 24:55.093
on foreign mission trips that he was taking pretending to be spreading the gospel for 12 years with one woman in Russia while he looked humble.

24:56.054 --> 25:04.142
The man who was so prideful and cocky and arrogant is still doing the ministry today that he was doing 20 years ago.

25:04.562 --> 25:05.623
What am I trying to say?

25:05.923 --> 25:08.106
You suck at judging, and so do I.

25:09.487 --> 25:12.690
We don't know who God is going to be using 10 years from now.

25:12.834 --> 25:15.098
We don't know who God is going to raise up.

25:15.539 --> 25:20.648
So while y'all are looking at me like you're confused about this, let me break it down a little bit finer.

25:21.069 --> 25:27.140
Some of the people you dated are proof of the fact that you are not very good at getting past the packaging.

25:28.763 --> 25:30.226
Let me break it down a little bit further.

25:30.402 --> 25:43.667
Some of the people you put in your phone that you knew you needed to block, but you ignored that little instinct that told you there is something about them, you cannot trust your own judgment this year.

25:43.707 --> 25:47.374
You cannot trust your fleshly, earthly judgment.

25:47.834 --> 25:51.922
When Israel trusted her judgment, she got Saul as king.

25:52.066 --> 25:54.829
David was a man after God's own heart.

25:55.270 --> 25:57.272
But even David had weeds.

25:57.492 --> 25:58.614
Ask Bathchiba.

25:59.194 --> 26:03.039
Even the man after God's own heart didn't always do it God's way.

26:03.539 --> 26:09.326
And what I'm trying to say, and I'm kind of going all around the barn to say it, so let me just land the plane.

26:09.606 --> 26:10.848
We all got weeds.

26:15.373 --> 26:16.774
We all got weeds.

26:18.116 --> 26:20.018
Say it out loud.

26:20.898 --> 26:22.882
Put the S at the end of that, just making sure.

26:22.902 --> 26:28.772
I'm talking about the biblical kind of weeds.

26:30.395 --> 26:31.477
It's called Darnell.

26:32.759 --> 26:34.903
Darnell, it's this type of weed.

26:34.943 --> 26:38.369
See, the Bible says… Can I preach about this for a moment?

26:39.171 --> 26:43.980
The Bible says that the man planted a good seed in his field.

26:44.020 --> 26:45.362
Everybody say his field.

26:46.178 --> 26:48.800
I'm gonna point this out to you over and over again as I preach today.

26:49.121 --> 26:50.322
It was his field.

26:50.682 --> 26:52.103
It belonged to the farmer.

26:52.463 --> 26:53.765
It belonged to the man.

26:54.125 --> 26:56.547
He planted the seed in his field.

26:56.587 --> 26:57.828
It was his property.

26:58.188 --> 27:01.371
It was his territory to do with it as he wished.

27:01.752 --> 27:04.154
He planted a good seed in the field.

27:04.514 --> 27:07.096
The seed was doing what it was supposed to do.

27:07.537 --> 27:08.597
It was growing.

27:08.898 --> 27:16.164
And since the seed was doing what it was supposed to do and growing, an enemy noticed the growth of the seed and said,

27:16.144 --> 27:20.729
If I don't do something about this seed, my enemy will triumph over me."

27:21.210 --> 27:30.460
So the Bible says that overnight, while men slept and enemy came and planted weeds among the wheat.

27:33.604 --> 27:34.805
Notice what he couldn't do.

27:35.146 --> 27:38.149
He could not pluck up what God had planted.

27:38.189 --> 27:45.938
He could not change what had already been done.

27:47.042 --> 27:53.368
He could not cause the seed that was in the ground to stop being what it was meant to be.

27:55.771 --> 27:58.253
He could not destroy the seed.

27:59.114 --> 28:06.842
The only strategy he had was to distract the harvesters.

28:06.882 --> 28:08.624
Here's the progression of growth in our life.

28:09.965 --> 28:15.090
We advance a little bit like the seed was doing, and then we get attacked.

28:16.706 --> 28:23.814
How many of y'all almost have to laugh at how quickly the devil attacked the very thing you were advancing in this year already?

28:23.875 --> 28:24.896
Just wave at me.

28:25.677 --> 28:26.938
It's almost comical, right?

28:27.779 --> 28:30.282
It's almost like two on the nose, like really devil?

28:31.644 --> 28:33.426
Like really, really like that.

28:33.486 --> 28:34.787
You're going to be that obvious.

28:34.827 --> 28:36.850
You're just going to do it right in my face like that.

28:37.471 --> 28:40.354
At least in the parable, the man snuck in and did it at night.

28:41.255 --> 28:43.698
Some of us, the devil's just doing it in broad daylight.

28:44.418 --> 28:46.860
just attacking things that are advancing.

28:48.282 --> 28:54.388
So now you're advancing, the seed is growing, and you're attacked.

28:54.408 --> 28:59.152
And when the enemy attacks you and what God is doing in you, you get distracted.

29:00.854 --> 29:02.836
He can't destroy the seed, it's not his.

29:04.498 --> 29:07.741
He can't destroy the seed, it's already planted.

29:09.182 --> 29:13.266
He can't destroy the seed, what God put in the seed is still in the seed.

29:14.594 --> 29:27.392
He doesn't have permission to do that, but what he can do is distract you so that you will destroy yourself.

29:27.472 --> 29:37.907
Some of the things that are attacking you in your life right now, the attack doesn't matter unless it distracts you from what God has called you.

29:39.309 --> 29:41.692
I'll break it down for you with a few pastoral examples.

29:42.173 --> 29:42.994
Thank you so much.

29:43.938 --> 29:44.900
It feels good to be wanted.

29:44.920 --> 29:45.861
It feels good to be loved.

29:45.881 --> 29:46.903
It feels good to be supported.

29:48.045 --> 29:59.183
But you have to preach through all kinds of seasons, and there have been seasons in this ministry where I have had to preach what God gave me to preach, even though I felt attacked.

29:59.523 --> 30:04.712
In my earlier years of preaching, I would become hyper-focused on any attack that was coming my way.

30:04.732 --> 30:05.774
I don't just mean critics.

30:06.114 --> 30:10.962
I mean any attack like if a staff member resigned, I would call it an attack.

30:12.098 --> 30:14.803
No, maybe they just need to move to Florida to take care of their parents.

30:14.843 --> 30:15.644
No, it's an attack.

30:16.405 --> 30:17.267
I rebuke the devil.

30:17.647 --> 30:18.509
What do you rebuke it?

30:18.529 --> 30:20.532
It's not an attack.

30:20.813 --> 30:24.118
It's an adjustment.

30:24.138 --> 30:25.520
You have to adapt.

30:25.540 --> 30:26.382
Life just happens.

30:27.123 --> 30:29.948
But there have been seasons, and I remembered one very specifically.

30:31.991 --> 30:35.497
I've been looking forward to sharing this with you because it was so fresh and so vivid.

30:36.379 --> 30:38.482
What was happening in our church was explosive.

30:38.978 --> 30:42.542
Much like the seed in the passage, it was growing, growing, growing.

30:43.042 --> 30:45.505
God planted this church in Charlotte in 2006.

30:45.685 --> 30:47.206
I didn't plant it.

30:47.446 --> 30:47.787
He did.

30:49.248 --> 30:51.250
What God plants, God protects.

30:52.652 --> 30:55.074
God was doing all kinds of miracles for us.

30:55.154 --> 30:57.276
If we needed a building, he opened a building.

30:57.937 --> 31:00.600
If we needed a volunteer, he sent a volunteer.

31:01.420 --> 31:03.462
If we needed funds, he would send people with money.

31:04.363 --> 31:07.026
God was just providing and protecting.

31:08.130 --> 31:14.057
But in one season of our ministry, and it was over 10 years ago, this vicious attack began.

31:14.097 --> 31:19.282
And if anybody was here at the time, you will remember several phases of the attack.

31:19.322 --> 31:29.834
The last phase of the attack was the hardest for me to stomach because they began to imply on news stories that were on the 11 o'clock news that at Elevation Church, we fake baptisms.

31:30.775 --> 31:37.202
In other words, they were saying that we have people pretending to be baptized, I guess just so we could put it on camera.

31:38.082 --> 31:46.775
Not only was that not true, but it was a direct assault against the most meaningful expression of faith that a person can make to be baptized.

31:47.576 --> 32:02.338
And I felt so attacked, not only on my own behalf, but on behalf of everyone who was going to work who had been baptized at this church, hearing the lie that had been perpetuated, the attack that had been waged saying, your baptism, was it fake?

32:03.159 --> 32:07.666
And I was praying about this one day, and I was asking God very specifically,

32:08.034 --> 32:12.261
something you may have been praying about a situation or an attack in your life as well.

32:12.661 --> 32:15.125
I prayed, God, make it stop.

32:17.989 --> 32:23.458
By this point there had been several attacks against our church, and this one just felt like too much.

32:24.199 --> 32:26.122
I said, God, make it stop.

32:26.963 --> 32:36.658
I will never forget what the Lord said to me in my spirit, not in audible words or not in a physical impression, but in a way he gave me a thought I have carried with me to this moment.

32:36.994 --> 32:38.275
I share it with you today."

32:39.016 --> 32:47.426
The Lord said, I can stop the attack, but if I stop the attack, I have to stop the impact that created it.

32:52.532 --> 32:53.713
Now you have to decide.

32:55.776 --> 33:01.082
Do you want the attack to stop bad enough to give up the impact that brought it?

33:02.403 --> 33:04.786
Because if you weren't baptizing anybody,

33:05.602 --> 33:08.746
They wouldn't be making up stories about your baptism.

33:10.649 --> 33:28.934
But maybe what God was doing in this church was so unbelievable that the enemy saw it and said, if they keep baptizing people like this, there's going to be a water shortage in Charlotte and a people shortage in hell.

33:29.675 --> 33:34.642
And so I got to plant a little lie to try to get them

33:35.010 --> 33:38.340
to stop doing what God started.

33:39.162 --> 33:44.498
But God said, if you want the impact, you got a man up.

33:44.994 --> 34:14.322
and button your pants and tighten your belt and lace your boots and open your Bible and open your mouth and take your next breath and lift your voice and lift your head and swing your sword in the name of the Lord and realize that he who began a good work in you will be faithful to bring a full circle till the day when the angels

34:14.466 --> 34:18.911
gather the tears to be burned in the fire.

34:27.300 --> 34:28.401
I wanted to tell you about that.

34:30.103 --> 34:34.128
I wanted to tell you that now that I'm through it, I'm glad they attacked me.

34:35.749 --> 34:36.110
I am.

34:37.051 --> 34:38.913
It set me free of some ego.

34:40.134 --> 34:41.756
I'm glad that happened.

34:42.617 --> 34:43.698
I wanted to happen again.

34:44.482 --> 34:46.065
I'm not asking for another one.

34:46.786 --> 34:49.770
I'm not saying if I went back in time, I would have walked that path.

34:51.032 --> 34:55.880
But there is a young man on our staff who runs my scriptures every week.

34:56.902 --> 34:58.985
As a matter of fact, put a scripture up there just in anyone.

34:59.005 --> 34:59.666
I don't care which one.

34:59.686 --> 35:02.831
Just put it up there and just put the week appeared.

35:03.132 --> 35:04.033
Circle the word appeared.

35:05.956 --> 35:06.457
Look at that.

35:08.420 --> 35:09.522
Why did I tell him to do that?

35:10.343 --> 35:12.146
Because he started coming to the church.

35:13.794 --> 35:20.923
Because he heard about the baptisms on the news from the attack.

35:22.024 --> 35:24.547
Y'all don't want to mess with me.

35:24.567 --> 35:33.238
And now he's the one helping me preach the Word, so God used their words as a weapon.

35:33.358 --> 35:35.260
Oh, God.

35:35.280 --> 35:37.803
And now let's talk about you.

35:37.823 --> 35:43.410
No weapon formed against you shall prosper.

35:44.226 --> 36:14.130
And every tongue that rises against you You shall condemn This is the heritage of the service of the Lord And their righteousness is from me So one thing the enemy didn't realize when he was planting those weeds Is that you can plant all the weeds you want to

36:14.306 --> 36:18.250
Devil, and let me just remind you this year, this year there will be weeds.

36:18.591 --> 36:22.095
There will be no weed-free week in your year this year.

36:23.857 --> 36:24.417
Sit back down.

36:26.259 --> 36:28.382
You know how we do these little New Year's slogans.

36:29.182 --> 36:30.304
Come alive in 25.

36:30.664 --> 36:38.453
It's going to get fixed in 26.

36:39.974 --> 36:40.975
No, it's not either.

36:41.236 --> 36:43.378
It's going to be mixed in 26.

36:44.066 --> 36:45.338
It's going to be some weeds.

36:46.187 --> 36:47.762
It's going to be some weeds.

36:47.970 --> 36:49.352
It's going to be some joy.

36:49.392 --> 36:51.314
It's going to be some mourning.

36:51.354 --> 36:53.076
It's going to be some weeping.

36:53.116 --> 36:54.758
It's going to be some reaping.

36:55.119 --> 36:56.320
It's going to be some friends.

36:56.741 --> 36:57.982
It's going to be some enemies.

36:58.403 --> 36:59.604
It's going to be some frenemies.

36:59.644 --> 37:13.100
You can't tell the difference till it's over, but don't judge it before God's done with it, because God might use some of this stuff in your life that you are asking him to remove, to reveal who he is in your life.

37:13.481 --> 37:17.746
And the only problem is if you start trying to pluck out

37:18.306 --> 37:21.791
weeds, you might mess around and remove the wheat.

37:28.021 --> 37:29.243
Y'all got enough or keep going?

37:33.349 --> 37:43.484
One thing I noticed in the text that was really powerful is that the master didn't panic about the attack.

37:43.504 --> 37:44.786
He was so cool about it.

37:45.154 --> 37:45.975
Read it again.

37:46.295 --> 37:48.878
Sir, now the servants are freaking out like we do.

37:49.439 --> 37:51.120
Sir, didn't you sow good seed in your field?

37:51.140 --> 37:51.681
Where does it come from?

37:51.701 --> 37:52.041
Who did this?

37:52.061 --> 37:52.522
What's going on?

37:52.602 --> 37:53.443
Is this a devil?

37:53.503 --> 37:54.184
Who's fault is this?

37:54.244 --> 37:57.407
Somebody did this.

37:59.650 --> 38:03.293
The master, because he represents God in the parable, look at this.

38:03.854 --> 38:05.276
He's like, an enemy did this.

38:10.641 --> 38:11.843
Because that's what an enemy does.

38:11.863 --> 38:15.026
That's what an enemy does.

38:16.674 --> 38:17.816
That's what a devil does.

38:17.836 --> 38:24.104
I read about a book that Mel Robbins wrote called The Let Them Theory.

38:25.165 --> 38:26.808
I didn't read the book, but I like the title.

38:28.109 --> 38:29.611
It's like people want to talk about you?

38:29.892 --> 38:30.433
Let them.

38:30.473 --> 38:33.457
Your kids want to leave without a coat and it's cold outside?

38:33.877 --> 38:34.478
Let them.

38:34.538 --> 38:41.387
They're not going to die of hypothermia.

38:41.427 --> 38:43.170
They will figure it out.

38:43.190 --> 38:44.251
Kids are resilient.

38:45.012 --> 38:46.354
They need a little frostbite.

38:47.874 --> 38:48.675
Let down.

38:48.735 --> 38:57.426
And I wonder if we could write one together today this year in your life called let him.

39:01.291 --> 39:02.713
Don't let the attack distract you.

39:03.114 --> 39:05.817
You give so much focus on how the devil is discouraging you.

39:05.857 --> 39:07.640
And now the discouragement is all you see everywhere.

39:09.883 --> 39:15.570
You got so many things going right in your life, so much wheat, but all you see is wheat.

39:16.578 --> 39:17.740
You're a little perfectionist.

39:18.921 --> 39:20.483
You're a little type A personality.

39:21.304 --> 39:22.906
You're a little enneagram number one.

39:22.986 --> 39:24.428
Just always could be better.

39:24.488 --> 39:27.032
Just, oh, man, I got to get these weeds out this year.

39:27.532 --> 39:29.234
No, you don't.

39:29.254 --> 39:29.955
And I'll tell you why.

39:30.536 --> 39:34.461
If Jesus' field wasn't weed-free, what makes you think yours is going to be?

39:37.185 --> 39:39.748
Jesus couldn't have a weed-free field, but you can.

39:39.788 --> 39:41.430
No.

39:42.552 --> 39:44.274
It's going to be mixed in 26.

39:46.210 --> 39:47.372
It's going to be mixed in 26.

39:47.652 --> 39:50.856
It's going to be at 8 a.m. in the morning.

39:50.876 --> 39:52.559
This is the day the Lord has made.

39:53.861 --> 39:56.144
It's going to be by 3 p.m. in the afternoon.

39:56.164 --> 39:58.127
My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?

39:58.187 --> 40:02.232
It's going to be weeds.

40:03.594 --> 40:06.298
Stop judging stuff before God is done with it.

40:09.482 --> 40:12.326
Stop judging stuff before the appointed time.

40:12.366 --> 40:15.090
Stop telling me graves into gardens and a good song.

40:17.058 --> 40:19.020
Stop telling me I tried it, it didn't work.

40:19.561 --> 40:22.123
And I'll just use a physical example, because we can all relate to it.

40:24.186 --> 40:43.666
When you work out and you haven't worked out in a while, not that you would know, the first thing that is going to indicate that you successfully completed the workout is a feeling of soreness that will feel like Satan himself.

40:43.842 --> 40:48.767
brought seven spirits to your body and invaded everything, but that just means you're growing.

40:50.709 --> 40:53.732
So now you're surprised that you're sore, but you wanted to grow.

40:53.752 --> 40:58.597
If there had been no wheat, there would have been no weeds.

41:00.639 --> 41:06.145
You're praying for God to use you, but you're surprised that you feel like you're empty on the inside.

41:06.425 --> 41:07.826
That's so he can fill you up again.

41:08.347 --> 41:11.410
And the promise of this year is not that it will be

41:11.522 --> 41:12.283
weed-free.

41:12.624 --> 41:34.053
I am not trying to be spirit-filled this year so that whatever is planted around me… You have to know that the Master is very, very methodical in what he plants.

41:35.075 --> 41:40.242
He knew from the moment he planted this seed that the enemy would attack him.

41:41.026 --> 41:46.094
Now, the master wasn't surprised the servants were, so they said, what do you want us to do about it?

41:46.495 --> 41:48.177
Do you want us to pluck it up?

41:49.599 --> 41:51.142
Do you want us to remove it?

41:52.103 --> 41:53.906
Do you want us to do something about that?

41:54.247 --> 42:00.537
I was reading a passage in 1 Kings, or maybe in 2 Samuel last week with Graham.

42:01.618 --> 42:02.980
Which scripture did I give you, Justin?

42:03.000 --> 42:04.262
2 Samuel or 1 Kings?

42:05.204 --> 42:06.205
We were reading about David.

42:06.586 --> 42:06.826
Yeah.

42:07.127 --> 42:09.170
One time, David was running through his

42:09.794 --> 42:17.121
His city he used to rule over from his son, Absalom, and his son was trying to take his crown from him.

42:17.902 --> 42:21.365
The son's name was Absalom, and David actually had to go flee from his own son.

42:22.065 --> 42:25.749
As he was leaving the city, he approached Bahuram.

42:26.209 --> 42:27.030
You couldn't pronounce it either.

42:27.370 --> 42:31.134
A man from the same clan as Saul's family came out from there.

42:31.174 --> 42:32.335
This is one of his enemies, right?

42:33.516 --> 42:39.762
His name was Shimei, son of Gerah, and he cursed as he came out.

42:40.642 --> 42:41.804
cursing at the king.

42:41.844 --> 42:47.173
Well, he pelted David and the king's officials with stones.

42:48.595 --> 42:52.622
Now, remember, David is pretty good with a stone, so this is a bad idea.

42:52.662 --> 42:56.629
Though all the troops in the special guard were on David's right and left.

42:56.649 --> 42:58.051
In other words, he could have done something about it.

42:58.332 --> 43:04.562
As he cursed, Shimea said, Get out, you murderer, you scoundrel.

43:05.314 --> 43:10.460
And the Lord has repaid you for all the blood you shed in the household of Saul, in whose place you have reigned.

43:10.800 --> 43:11.621
God's getting you back.

43:11.922 --> 43:15.966
The Lord has given the kingdom into the hands of your son, Absalom.

43:15.986 --> 43:21.853
You have come to ruin because you are a murderer, planting all these seeds of doubt in David's mind.

43:21.873 --> 43:27.460
Then Abishai, which one of David's guys said to the king, why should this dead dog curse my Lord, the king?

43:27.760 --> 43:29.742
Let me go over and cut off his head.

43:30.683 --> 43:33.106
But the king, David said,

43:33.474 --> 43:35.176
What does this have to do with you?

43:36.138 --> 43:41.065
If he's cursing because the Lord said to him, curse David, who can ask?

43:41.525 --> 43:42.467
Why do you do this?

43:43.308 --> 43:50.137
David then said to Abishai and all his officials, my son, my own flesh and blood is trying to kill me.

43:50.338 --> 43:51.960
In other words, I got bigger problems.

43:53.121 --> 43:55.485
I got bigger things to deal with than this dude.

43:55.885 --> 43:59.250
And I came to remind you, you've got bigger priorities.

43:59.522 --> 44:02.146
You've got too much to do to be offended by them.

44:02.567 --> 44:07.415
You've got bigger fish to fry than this guy whose name I can't even pronounce.

44:07.815 --> 44:08.637
You're David.

44:09.498 --> 44:11.541
How much more than this Benjamin?

44:11.602 --> 44:12.523
Leave him alone.

44:13.264 --> 44:14.727
Let him curse.

44:16.149 --> 44:17.351
You want us to do something about it?

44:17.431 --> 44:17.631
No.

44:18.312 --> 44:18.853
Let him.

44:19.995 --> 44:22.379
Let him curse, for the Lord has told him to.

44:23.140 --> 44:26.706
It may be… Oh, this is an anointed.

44:26.786 --> 44:40.184
Verse, if you've been under attack and the enemy is pelting you with rocks and stones and it may even be coming at the expense of your own dignity and you are asking yourself, what do I do about this attack?

44:40.224 --> 44:49.136
David said, it may be that the Lord will look upon my misery and restore to me his covenant blessing instead of his curse today.

44:49.537 --> 44:53.522
In other words, what David is saying is that he cannot curse.

44:53.730 --> 44:57.755
what God has already blessed, so let him.

44:58.816 --> 45:02.561
He cannot destroy what has God's DNA.

45:02.961 --> 45:06.045
He cannot steal what God has spoke.

45:06.406 --> 45:10.030
He cannot negate what God has established.

45:10.431 --> 45:13.695
He cannot cancel out what God has called.

45:14.135 --> 45:19.442
How many different ways do you need me to say it to get you to see it won't work?

45:20.258 --> 45:21.163
Let him come.

45:21.706 --> 45:23.154
Let the flood rage.

45:23.174 --> 45:24.883
God will lift up a standard.

45:25.365 --> 45:26.994
It won't work.

45:27.170 --> 45:29.092
Don't let the attack distract you.

45:29.433 --> 45:31.295
Don't let it get you out of your character.

45:31.636 --> 45:33.378
Don't let it get you out of your joy.

45:33.738 --> 45:35.340
Don't let it get you out of your peace.

45:35.781 --> 45:38.865
Sit there and whistle a worship song if you can't sing one.

45:39.486 --> 45:41.788
Lift your toe if you can't lift your hands.

45:42.429 --> 45:44.973
Do a body weight squat if you can't do a real one.

45:45.413 --> 45:55.666
Do something, but whatever you do, remember that if it started with God, it is sustained by God, and there is nothing the enemy can plant.

45:55.778 --> 46:01.042
Jeremiah said before I was born he called me and sent me apart

46:01.186 --> 46:04.149
That means I know the enemy has been busy in your life.

46:04.529 --> 46:05.870
He's been speaking to you.

46:06.210 --> 46:07.772
He's been sabotaging you.

46:08.092 --> 46:22.805
He's been distracting you, trying to get you off your course, trying to get you out of your flow, trying to get you out of your calling, trying to get you out of your nature, trying to get you out of your kindness, trying to bring you back to bitterness, trying to plant weeds where there's wheat.

46:23.085 --> 46:31.172
But there's one thing that the enemy should have realized that he didn't realize, and he would have saved his energy and realized that the weeds

46:31.152 --> 46:40.766
weren't worth planting, because you've got to remember no matter what the enemy plants in your life, God got there first.

46:49.699 --> 46:53.565
And he prepares a table for you in the presence of your enemies.

46:55.808 --> 46:59.634
So let the devil try, because it must be

47:00.482 --> 47:05.568
If God isn't removing those weeds… How many can picture some weeds that are in your life as I speak this word?

47:07.710 --> 47:15.278
Every weed-free person run to this altar right now because you have the weed of delusion.

47:19.803 --> 47:20.584
Am I right, man?

47:20.644 --> 47:29.394
And the one thing about it, Graham… Check this out, G. The type of weeds that were growing, you couldn't tell they weren't wheat until they had grown a little bit.

47:30.594 --> 47:35.899
They looked exactly the same until the head came up, and then they were like, oh no, this is not wheat.

47:35.919 --> 47:36.660
This is a weed.

47:38.102 --> 47:39.043
And sometimes you don't know.

47:40.304 --> 47:41.345
Sometimes you don't know.

47:42.746 --> 47:45.850
I'm never going back to the way I was.

47:46.470 --> 47:48.492
Look at what the Lord has done.

47:48.973 --> 47:51.235
I'm never going back to the way.

47:51.595 --> 47:53.117
I love the video.

47:53.317 --> 47:58.002
I know the kids just screaming at the camera, but what if they were singing it like just like

47:58.178 --> 48:01.783
Just for real though, like, look at what the Lord has done.

48:02.244 --> 48:05.649
I'm never going back, but I'm still going cussed.

48:05.669 --> 48:06.249
You know what I'm saying?

48:09.013 --> 48:10.976
Look at what the Lord has done.

48:11.457 --> 48:14.421
I'm never going back, but I still get drunk.

48:14.802 --> 48:19.008
Because what we're saying is, look at what the Lord has done.

48:19.428 --> 48:22.232
I'm never going back, but I'm still going lust.

48:22.272 --> 48:24.115
You know, just whatever y'all struggle with.

48:25.477 --> 48:26.418
The fact is,

48:28.002 --> 48:33.210
What's really going on in our hearts sometimes doesn't match what's coming out of our mouths.

48:35.854 --> 48:43.485
We really do want to grow, and we really do want to be free, and we really do want to be more loving.

48:43.505 --> 48:56.704
But the enemy isn't going to stand by and watch you grow without attempting to plant something alongside your destiny that will disrupt it.

48:56.724 --> 48:57.906
I just want to remind you.

48:58.370 --> 49:01.074
that the attack is a distraction.

49:02.215 --> 49:09.505
God knew when he planted you that what he gave you was stronger than what would come against you.

49:19.419 --> 49:21.121
Look at what the Lord has done in your life.

49:22.963 --> 49:24.946
Look how far he has already brought you.

49:25.666 --> 49:27.649
How many can say, I have a testimony.

49:27.689 --> 49:29.351
God has done so much in my life.

49:29.651 --> 49:30.332
It's amazing.

49:31.294 --> 49:36.420
You would say that, but it came with weeds, didn't it?

49:38.443 --> 49:44.852
You have been believing the lie lately that you have got to get rid of all the weeds before you can enjoy the wheat.

49:45.673 --> 49:46.314
It's a lie.

49:47.295 --> 49:48.136
I come against it.

49:49.318 --> 49:55.666
I break the spirit of depression off of your soul that has been telling you that you cannot worship

49:55.778 --> 49:58.742
While you still have weeds, we all have weeds.

49:59.303 --> 50:03.288
It would surprise you what the person next to you is struggling with.

50:04.289 --> 50:07.634
And just because you can't see the weeds doesn't mean they're not real.

50:07.674 --> 50:15.945
But have you come to a point in your life where all you are seeing in this season is the weeds?

50:17.327 --> 50:22.994
Have you got one kid that is in trouble and you have failed to appreciate the two that are doing good?

50:23.970 --> 50:27.822
That means you have become too weed focused.

50:29.507 --> 50:33.298
Have you got nine things in your body that are working well?

50:33.506 --> 50:46.744
But the one thing that is not working right just causes you to obsess, and you are Googling every possible thing that might be wrong with you and taking out every life insurance policy because you've got a headache one Thursday.

50:47.185 --> 50:55.997
Are you letting one headache really make you stop believing that God is my healer and that God is my sustainer and that God is my source?

50:56.398 --> 51:02.546
I'm telling you, whatever the enemy plants in your life is not more powerful than what God planted.

51:03.298 --> 51:05.657
Because the Bible said he planted good seed.

51:06.545 --> 51:08.178
Somebody say I'm good seed.

51:08.834 --> 51:15.940
I'm good seed, and all things work together for the good of those who love the Lord and are called according to his purpose.

51:16.240 --> 51:27.510
So this week, I want you to think a little bit less about the weeds and a little bit more about the wheat, because when the passage starts, we've got wheat and we've got weeds.

51:27.951 --> 51:33.055
But at the end of the passage, one is going to be burned and one is going to be in the barn.

51:33.455 --> 51:36.798
And I came to declare today, the fire will not burn you.

51:37.179 --> 51:38.820
You're going to the barn, baby.

51:38.800 --> 51:40.342
You belong to God.

51:40.702 --> 51:42.344
You are God's child.

51:42.644 --> 51:44.266
You are God's planting.

51:44.546 --> 51:45.907
You are God's oak.

51:46.288 --> 51:48.450
You are God's masterpiece.

51:48.970 --> 51:50.252
I belong to God.

51:50.732 --> 51:52.154
Try your best, devil.

51:52.554 --> 51:53.695
It won't work.

51:53.715 --> 52:01.443
As a matter of fact, my God might use the thing that you are using to curse me and bless me even better.

52:02.004 --> 52:04.306
God might do something out of this,

52:04.482 --> 52:15.375
So go ahead, hit me with your best shot, but everything you do has to go through the cross of Jesus Christ, and he'll begin a good work.

52:18.278 --> 52:21.962
We'll be faithful to complete it.

52:21.982 --> 52:24.946
Stop judging stuff before God is done.

52:25.326 --> 52:26.908
I asked one parent the other day.

52:27.228 --> 52:32.114
They said, the kid that gave me the most trouble ended up bringing me the most blessings.

52:32.226 --> 52:34.868
You can't judge this thing while it's still growing.

52:35.229 --> 52:38.151
You can't label this thing while it's still in process.

52:38.551 --> 52:48.060
You cannot categorize your life based on the way you feel right now, and you cannot quit 11 days into January just because it's mixed in 26.

52:49.061 --> 52:49.781
Nah, baby.

52:50.021 --> 52:51.763
The Lord is at my right hand.

52:52.123 --> 52:53.945
The Lord stood by my side.

52:54.385 --> 52:55.506
Many deserted me.

52:55.887 --> 52:56.967
God never did.

52:57.448 --> 52:58.449
I got battles.

52:58.849 --> 52:59.890
I got blessings.

53:00.310 --> 53:01.131
I got wheat.

53:01.571 --> 53:02.212
I got wheat.

53:02.192 --> 53:22.047
I got goodness I got mercy and they follow me all the days of my life So all I wanted to tell you today is don't let the attack Distract you That's what it is.

53:22.127 --> 53:25.874
It's a distraction You have been growing

53:26.562 --> 53:28.064
You've got what it takes to grow.

53:28.344 --> 53:30.867
You've got what it takes to make this decision.

53:31.147 --> 53:33.169
You have got what it takes to do the job.

53:33.450 --> 53:35.432
You've got what it takes to learn the skills.

53:35.712 --> 53:38.755
You've got what it takes to do the inner work and get some healing.

53:38.775 --> 53:40.938
You've got what it takes because you've got God.

53:43.441 --> 53:45.743
You're in the field he wanted you to be in.

53:49.407 --> 53:52.791
And God knew there was going to be a fight when he put you in that field.

53:54.593 --> 53:55.634
Don't tell me he didn't.

53:56.354 --> 53:56.975
He's God.

53:58.798 --> 53:59.539
I'm built for it.

54:01.603 --> 54:02.043
High five.

54:02.083 --> 54:03.906
Three people say you're built for it too.

54:05.569 --> 54:06.170
Built for it.

54:08.073 --> 54:09.395
Yeah, man.

54:09.415 --> 54:10.016
Built for it.

54:11.859 --> 54:13.783
You know what I almost called the message, bro?

54:14.904 --> 54:15.726
I almost called it.

54:17.188 --> 54:18.390
Don't burn your bread.

54:22.056 --> 54:23.218
Don't burn your bread.

54:24.738 --> 54:40.239
The wheat has the potential in it to be bread if you don't pluck it up and throw it into the fire, if you don't give up on what it can be because of what it is right now and what's against it.

54:41.320 --> 54:42.221
Don't burn your bread.

54:42.241 --> 54:44.765
I didn't call it that.

54:45.986 --> 54:47.168
I almost called the message.

54:47.188 --> 54:48.830
This is my other almost called the message.

54:49.851 --> 54:51.954
Look at your neighbor say, Don't pluck it up.

54:58.626 --> 55:11.045
But I decided that I would just tell you, stand to your feet, don't let the attack distract you.

55:12.848 --> 55:15.251
Because if you don't let it distract you, it can't destroy you.

55:16.053 --> 55:17.535
The Word of God is incorruptible seed.

55:18.236 --> 55:20.900
You've been born again by imperishable seed.

55:20.920 --> 55:23.664
Don't let it distract you.

55:25.046 --> 55:27.570
You make an advance, you get attacked.

55:28.066 --> 55:29.568
You get attacked, you get distracted.

55:30.028 --> 55:31.710
You get distracted, you get destroyed.

55:32.010 --> 55:37.676
But if you can focus on where God is growing you, put your hand over your heart.

55:40.098 --> 55:41.079
Say this is good soil.

55:43.001 --> 55:44.123
Say this is God's soil.

55:45.684 --> 55:50.589
There's something that God spoke to you that you haven't really been able to get in touch with lately because you've been so distracted.

55:51.590 --> 55:52.772
You have been so distracted.

55:52.852 --> 55:55.154
It has been a long, long time.

55:55.394 --> 55:58.178
since you've been able to have clarity about what God spoke to you.

55:58.618 --> 56:02.604
And you found your broken focus leading to a lack of peace now, as it always happens.

56:03.345 --> 56:09.754
But if we can get back to the God who put it in you to begin with, you are going to survive whatever attack the enemy sends against it.

56:09.774 --> 56:11.997
It can't be stronger than God.

56:12.418 --> 56:14.360
It can't be stronger than his word.

56:14.741 --> 56:16.503
It can't be better than him.

56:16.523 --> 56:17.805
It can't be bigger than him.

56:18.106 --> 56:19.087
It's not possible.

56:20.729 --> 56:21.711
But you've been distracted.

56:23.293 --> 56:24.114
So now, Lord,

56:26.306 --> 56:37.561
Our hearts are yours.

56:39.324 --> 56:40.225
Our lives are yours.

56:41.407 --> 56:42.328
Our dreams are yours.

56:43.450 --> 56:44.391
Our plans are yours.

56:45.592 --> 56:46.614
Our future is yours.

56:48.296 --> 56:50.760
I thank you for where you planted me as a seed, God.

56:52.722 --> 56:55.506
I thank you for where you planted each and every one of these people.

56:56.450 --> 57:07.927
I think for the gifts you gave them, the abilities you gave them, the talent you gave them, the personality you gave them, the unique struggles and challenges that have formed them and forged them in the fire of trials to make them strong and ready for what they're going through now.

57:08.729 --> 57:09.490
They will not burn.

57:10.571 --> 57:19.806
They'll be like those Hebrew boys who went into the fire and said, even if God doesn't get us out, he'll join us right up in it, because I'm good seed.

57:20.827 --> 57:23.671
I'm good seed.

57:23.691 --> 57:25.394
Lord, I want to pray today for the person

57:25.954 --> 57:27.556
who has never placed their faith in you.

57:29.399 --> 57:31.762
Would you just join me in this prayer as a church?

57:31.782 --> 57:34.546
I'm going to pray for someone who needs to give their life to Jesus Christ.

57:34.726 --> 57:41.996
Right now, it is very possible that the reason God brought you here today or the reason you joined us online is for this moment.

57:43.098 --> 57:47.684
If you see, it's not by might nor by power that we become strong in the Lord.

57:47.744 --> 57:47.925
No.

57:49.707 --> 57:51.890
The seed was good because of who planted it.

57:53.890 --> 58:01.198
It's time for you to stop playing around with your life and waiting on one day when it's more convenient to live for God.

58:01.278 --> 58:01.859
No.

58:01.879 --> 58:04.422
Now is your moment of salvation.

58:04.482 --> 58:07.045
Today is your moment of change.

58:09.007 --> 58:11.029
I don't want you to face the fire of judgment.

58:11.089 --> 58:22.642
I don't want you to live your life apart from God, and neither does God, and that's why he sent Jesus, the perfect seed, the one who gave his life on the cross and rose again that you could have life.

58:23.202 --> 58:25.024
Now in this moment, I want to pray with you.

58:26.205 --> 58:34.132
The Bible says that if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.

58:34.152 --> 58:35.073
It's not by works.

58:36.134 --> 58:37.916
It's by grace you are saved through faith.

58:39.497 --> 58:45.223
Right now, if you'll pray this prayer and mean it with your heart, God will hear you and God will save you.

58:46.163 --> 58:49.527
You will be born again, and this can be your new beginning.

58:49.647 --> 58:53.170
We're going to pray out loud, repeating after me as a church.

58:53.538 --> 58:56.402
for the benefit of those who are coming to Christ in this moment.

58:56.702 --> 58:57.444
Repeat after me.

58:57.864 --> 59:03.933
Heavenly Father, today is my day of salvation.

59:05.114 --> 59:16.110
I am a sinner in need of a Savior, and I believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God and the Savior of the world.

59:17.352 --> 59:21.778
And today, I make Jesus the Lord of my life

59:22.754 --> 59:29.803
I believe he died that I would be forgiven and rose again to give me life.

59:30.864 --> 59:33.127
I receive this new life.

59:34.108 --> 59:36.451
This is my new beginning.

59:37.513 --> 59:39.675
I am a child of God.

59:40.536 --> 59:44.742
On the count of three, shoot your hand up if you prayed that one, two, three.

59:44.822 --> 59:46.104
I want to celebrate with you.

59:46.784 --> 59:47.605
Praise the Lord.

59:48.567 --> 59:49.308
Praise the Lord.

59:50.369 --> 59:51.250
That's beautiful.

59:52.482 --> 59:53.704
Praise the Lord online.

59:54.465 --> 59:56.207
You can just put it in the comments.

59:56.227 --> 59:58.390
I receive Jesus.

59:59.472 --> 01:00:01.755
Come on, let's clap our hands all over the room.

01:00:01.835 --> 01:00:03.638
Everybody, everybody, everybody.

01:00:05.120 --> 01:00:08.905
Come on, let's thank God for all the decisions that were made today.

01:00:10.447 --> 01:00:11.408
God is so good.

01:00:13.331 --> 01:00:15.855
Well, Campus Passers, you can have it.

01:00:16.375 --> 01:00:18.839
Grab hands with the person next to you here, Valentine.

01:00:19.460 --> 01:00:21.202
Look at him and tell him, don't pluck it up.

01:00:23.650 --> 01:00:25.252
Because God is not through with you yet.

01:00:27.235 --> 01:00:29.980
Another day to be in the presence of God.

01:00:30.460 --> 01:00:30.981
Come on, Holly.

01:00:31.001 --> 01:00:31.883
I ain't got no hand to hold.

01:00:34.767 --> 01:00:38.332
It's going to be an amazing year in your life, babe.

01:00:38.352 --> 01:00:38.693
Yeah.

01:00:39.374 --> 01:00:45.463
God's going to give you wisdom, strength, encouragement, stamina.

01:00:46.685 --> 01:00:49.970
God's going to do that for each and every one of these people that we pastor to.

01:00:51.170 --> 01:00:54.414
Look at your neighbor and say, God is going to do that for you too.

01:00:57.699 --> 01:00:58.800
Tell him he's going to meet you.

01:01:00.362 --> 01:01:01.223
He's going to feel you.

01:01:03.206 --> 01:01:04.367
He's going to carry you.

01:01:06.250 --> 01:01:07.211
He's going to keep you.

01:01:09.534 --> 01:01:10.415
Tell him you're going to grow.

01:01:11.577 --> 01:01:11.897
Come on.

01:01:11.937 --> 01:01:12.898
Tell him like a trainer.

01:01:13.139 --> 01:01:13.900
You're going to grow.

01:01:15.322 --> 01:01:18.706
Tell him like they need to do two more reps. Tell him you're going to grow.

01:01:19.714 --> 01:01:25.922
Look at him and shout, say, don't plunk it up.

01:01:26.703 --> 01:01:28.626
Don't let the attack distract you.

01:01:28.646 --> 01:01:30.468
It's a sign you're on course.

01:01:30.809 --> 01:01:32.731
It's a sign you're significant.

01:01:32.971 --> 01:01:35.415
It's a sign God's got you.

01:01:35.435 --> 01:01:43.986
And now unto him, lift your hands, who is able to do immeasurably more than you ask, think, or imagine.

01:01:44.066 --> 01:01:45.588
according to his power.

01:01:45.908 --> 01:01:46.669
Whose power?

01:01:47.090 --> 01:01:49.793
His power that works mightily in us.

01:01:50.334 --> 01:01:56.942
To him be glory through Christ Jesus in the church now and forever.

01:01:57.783 --> 01:01:59.826
Say amen.

01:01:59.846 --> 01:02:02.589
Say amen again.

01:02:02.609 --> 01:02:03.690
Goodbye.

01:02:03.710 --> 01:02:05.793
